    <h2 class="text-3xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 mb-4 leading-tight">Human onboarding and agent onboarding are the same problem.</h2>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-500 mb-12 max-w-2xl">A new hire who doesn't know who to report to, what they own, or how to escalate will fail. A new AI agent with the same gaps will fail faster -- and break more things on the way down.</p>

    <!-- Comparison Table -->
    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-xl border border-gray-200">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="bg-gray-50">
            <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-bold text-gray-900 border-b">Onboarding Need</th>
            <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-bold text-gray-900 border-b">Human Employee</th>
            <th class="px-6 py-4 text-left font-bold text-otp-600 border-b">AI Agent (via OOS)</th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
          <tr>
            <td class="px-6 py-4 font-medium text-gray-900">Who does what</td>
